            <a class="name">Dan</a> 
           </div> 
           <p class="cmt_cnt">Hi Sandra <br />I am not clear what you are saying. <br /> <br />As far as I understand Foreign Experts certificates are issued for a particular job contract. They are not transferable, but can be updated for a new contract with the same employer. <br /> <br />Also, every province has its own FE Bureau. The FE Bureau for th province you are wanting to work in will need to vet candidates applications (vet both candidate and employer). Only Guandong Government will have jurisdiction over contracts in Guandong. If you move to any new province you need new certification. <br /> <br />China is so big, and the government so large, you need to think of the Provinces almost as separate states, in terms of administration.</p> 
