           <p class="cmt_cnt">As a fresh grad you will not be in any position to apply for higher level jobs anywhere. To be fair, you have nothing to offer but your degree and your enthusiasm. And enthusiastic graduates are 10 a penny here. <br /> <br />The truth is that in China there is a glut of highly educated people who are fluent in both English and Mandarin. They also understand Chinese culture, and Chinese business culture. They are prepared to work long hours for little money in order to climb the ladder. <br /> <br />Do you think you are ready to compete at this level? <br /> <br />Sorry if this sounds blunt.</p> 
